					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13863497#post-4819720</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13863497/scp-5917#post-4819720</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 16 Nov 2020 06:23:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>not_a_seagull</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3009022</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I’m going back and forth on this one. I’m going to leave a tentative upvote here, but I might come back later and change it.</p> <p>The worldbuilding here is its greatest strength. It reminds me of the plastic knife scp whose number I can’t remember, in that it feels quite fleshed out. The execution here is also tightened up from the draft I read, and it’s quite a more enjoyable read.</p> <p>The execution is also my biggest reason I considered downvoting. It still jumps around quite a bit, which makes it feel jarring at points. The ending also leaves quite a bit to be desired; the ending lines don’t sting to me, and the dialogue is a bit purple for my tastes.</p> <p>+1 for now.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
